# Plan: Add Stepper Compound Component to shadcn/ui

## Context

The task is to add a new `Stepper` compound component to the shadcn/ui v4 registry. Steppers are multi-step progress indicators used in wizards, onboarding flows, and checkout processes. No existing component files are to be modified — only new files created and registry entries appended.

---

## Patterns Confirmed from Codebase Exploration

| Pattern | Source |
|---|---|
| `"use client"` at line 1 | carousel.tsx, tabs.tsx, accordion.tsx |
| `import * as React from "react"` | carousel.tsx |
| `React.createContext<T \| null>(null)` | carousel.tsx line 33 |
| `useContext` guard with throw | carousel.tsx lines 35–43 |
| `data-slot="..."` on every element | all components |
| `data-orientation={orientation}` | tabs.tsx line 17 |
| `data-state={state}` as data-attribute | accordion.tsx, tabs.tsx |
| `React.ComponentProps<"div">` for prop types | carousel.tsx line 53 |
| Named exports block at bottom | carousel.tsx lines 234–241 |
| `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` | all components |
| No default exports | all components |
| Function declarations (not arrow functions) | all components |

---

## Critical Files

| File | Action |
|---|---|
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` | **Create** (new component) |
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` | **Create** (new example) |
